$ Oracle hint: OPT_PARAM
@ opt_param

`opt_param` sets the value of a limited set of → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters (which are all related to the → development/databases/Oracle/optimizer) for the duration of the SQL statement.
The syntax is:
code {
/*+ opt_param(<parameter_name> [,] <parameter_value>) */
code }
For example: `/*+ opt_param('_optimizer_adaptive_plans', 'false') */` or `/*+ opt_param('_parallel_syspls_obey_force', 'false') */`.


sa:

  The init parameter → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/optimizer/features_enable[`optimizer_features_enable`] has a → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/hints/list/optimizer_features_enable`[corresponding hint with the same name].

  Other → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/hints[hints] such as `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL/hints/list/opt/estimate`.

  MOS Note 377333.1
